{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Wireframe"], "type": "title", "extent": [93, 107], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [107, 190], "text": ["Constructs polygonal tubes around polylines, creating renderable geometry."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [190, 320], "text": ["The Wireframe operation converts edges to tubes and points to spheres, creating the look of a wire frame structure in rendering."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [320, 383], "text": ["Wireframe works only with polygons and/or particles as input."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [394, 589], "text": ["Use the ", {"text": ["Poly Wire SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/polywire", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/polywire"}, " to create more complex tube geometry from curves, with smoother bends and intersections than Wireframe, especially for ", {"text": ["L-systems"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/lsystem", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/lsystem"}, "."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [589, 701], "text": ["Use the ", {"text": ["Convert Line SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/convertline", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/convertline"}, " to create a line segment for each edge in incoming polygons."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [701, 848], "text": ["Use the ", {"text": ["Ends SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/ends", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/ends"}, " set to Unwrap U to open each of the closed polygons into an open curve that includes the start and end points."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Tips"], "extent": [383, 394], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [871, 910], "text": ["Subset of geometry to convert."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Group"], "role": "i